Meeting 4.1 – System Evaluation
Date: 23 March 2026
Time: 10:00 – 10:30
Attendees: Project Developer
Agenda:
Evaluate overall system performance
Identify limitations
Discussion:
The system was reviewed to evaluate its overall performance and efficiency. It was observed that while the Binary 
Search Tree performs efficiently in most cases, its performance can degrade when the tree becomes unbalanced. This
issue was analysed, and the impact on search time was discussed. Possible improvements, including the use of
self-balancing trees, were considered.
Outcome:
System limitations identified
Improvement areas documented
